Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Israeli Arab delegation headed by Knesset 
Member [MK] 'Abd-al-Wahhab Darawshah will be allowed to set out 
for Syria on 27 February via Cairo to deliver its condolences to 
President Hafiz al-Asad over the death of his son, Egyptian 
Ambassador Muhammad Basyuni informed MK Darawshah last night. 
He also told him that President al-Asad and the Syrian 
Government welcome the arrival of the Israeli Arab delegation. 
Our correspondent Qaysar Kabha reports that the delegation will 
consist of 50 members, including MK's Darawshah and Talib 
al-Sani'. The Egyptian Government will issue each delegate a 
one-time laissez-passer to enter Syria. 

